<ol class="list-inside list-decimal whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;li]:ps-6" data-streamdown="ordered-list">
<li class="py-1 [&amp;&gt;p]:inline" data-streamdown="list-item"><span class="font-semibold" data-streamdown="strong">No build step</span> - Open in browser and it works. No <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">npm install</code>, no Tailwind compiler.</li>
<li class="py-1 [&amp;&gt;p]:inline" data-streamdown="list-item"><span class="font-semibold" data-streamdown="strong">CSS Variables</span> = Change <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">--primary: #FF5733</code> once and your whole site rebrands.</li>
<li class="py-1 [&amp;&gt;p]:inline" data-streamdown="list-item"><span class="font-semibold" data-streamdown="strong">Vanilla JS only</span> - 20 lines. No jQuery, no React. Anyone can read it.</li>
<li class="py-1 [&amp;&gt;p]:inline" data-streamdown="list-item"><span class="font-semibold" data-streamdown="strong">Semantic HTML</span> - <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">&lt;main&gt;</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">&lt;section&gt;</code> instead of <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">&lt;div&gt;</code> soup. Better for SEO + screen readers.</li>
<li class="py-1 [&amp;&gt;p]:inline" data-streamdown="list-item"><span class="font-semibold" data-streamdown="strong">Performance</span> - Dropped 100KB+ base64 image. Removed Tailwind CDN. Page loads 3x faster.</li>
<li class="py-1 [&amp;&gt;p]:inline" data-streamdown="list-item"><span class="font-semibold" data-streamdown="strong">Maintainable</span> - All styles in one <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">&lt;style&gt;</code> block. Comments separate sections. Easy to find stuff 6 months later.</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="mt-6 mb-2 font-semibold text-xl" data-streamdown="heading-3"><span class="font-semibold" data-streamdown="strong">Next steps for you</span></h3>
<ol class="list-inside list-decimal whitespace-normal [&amp;&gt;li]:ps-6" data-streamdown="ordered-list">
<li class="py-1 [&amp;&gt;p]:inline" data-streamdown="list-item"><span class="font-semibold" data-streamdown="strong">Extract that base64 image</span>: Save it as <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">assets/brian.jpg</code> and replace the <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">src</code>. Want me to decode it for you?</li>
<li class="py-1 [&amp;&gt;p]:inline" data-streamdown="list-item"><span class="font-semibold" data-streamdown="strong">Add your real sections</span>: I stubbed <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">header</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">hero</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm" data-streamdown="inline-code">services</code>. Send me the rest of your HTML and I'll convert it.</li>
